      <hedline>
        <hl1>Literary Massacre</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Don Rauf letter says what is shocking about Bret Easton Ellis's book American Psycho is that literary cognoscente marketed it as literature (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to Rick Marin's article '' 'American Psycho': Sliced. Diced. Back.'' (April 9), I don't think people were so shocked by the content of Bret Easton Ellis's book as by the fact that the literary cognoscenti were marketing this ham-fisted (and headed) fluff as ''literature.'' If you repackaged ''The Texas Chainsaw Massacre'' as a novel, dumbed it down and then touted it as high literature, you'd get the same reaction of outrage today.</p>
        <p>DON RAUF  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
